casebody.data:
No. 30,

Misc.

Gregory v. United States. Petitioner pro se. Solicitor General Sobeloff, Assistant Attorney General Olney, Beatrice Rosenberg and Felicia Dubrovsky for the United States.

On petition for writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit.

Per Curiam:

The petition for writ of certiorari is granted. The judgment is vacated and the case is remanded to the Court of Appeals for consideration on the merits.
